1 hydraulic features of the flood control system; and
2 WHEREAS, the accumulation of sediment in the basin has contributed to reduced
3 water depths, impaired water circulation, and the formation of spoil banks and sediment
4 deposits that restrict natural hydrologic connectivity; and
5 WHEREAS, reduced water flow and increased sedimentation can degrade water
6 quality, increase stagnation, alter nutrient dynamics, and contribute to the loss of aquatic
7 habitat; and
8 WHEREAS, these changes may adversely affect fish populations and the
9 productivity of commercial fisheries, including crawfish and finfish, as well as recreational
10 fishing opportunities relied upon by residents and visitors; and
11 WHEREAS, the continued accumulation of sediment within the basin may also affect
12 flood conveyance capacity, navigation channels, and the long-term ecological sustainability
13 of the Atchafalaya Basin; and
14 WHEREAS, a comprehensive review of sediment sources, transport mechanisms,
15 and basin management strategies is necessary to develop effective solutions to reduce
16 sediment inputs and restore water flow and ecological function within the basin.
17 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
18 create a joint legislative committee to study the water quality of the Atchafalaya Basin to
19 include the causes and effects of sediment accumulation in the Atchafalaya Basin and
20 Atchafalaya Basin Floodway System, to evaluate impacts on water flow, water quality,
21 habitat, and commercial and recreational fisheries, and to recommend strategies to reduce
22 sediment entering the basin and to remove accumulated sediment to restore ecological and
23 hydrological function.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the joint legislative committee created herein
25 shall be composed of members of the Senate who represent Districts 17, 21, and 22 and
26 members of the House of Representatives who represent Districts 18, 46, 50, 60 and 96.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the president of the Senate shall name one of the
28 Senate members of the committee as the chairperson for the limited purpose of calling the
29 first meeting, and at the first meeting, the members shall elect a chairman and other officers
