DIGEST
SCR 29 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Kleinpeter
Creates a joint legislative committee to study and make recommendations relative to the
water quality of the Atchafalaya Basin, including the causes and effects of sediment
accumulation and its impacts on hydrology, habitat, and fisheries.
Provides that the joint legislative committee shall be composed of specified members of the
Senate and House of Representatives representing designated legislative districts and that
the president of the Senate shall designate a Senate member to call the first meeting, after
which the committee shall elect its officers.
Provides that the committee shall have the powers otherwise provided by law and legislative
rules, that members shall receive per diem and mileage, and that staff support shall be
provided by the Senate Committee on Natural Resources and the House Committee on
Natural Resources and Environment.
Authorizes the committee to request data, technical assistance, and recommendations from
specified state and federal agencies, academic institutions, stakeholders, and other interested
parties involved in the management of the Atchafalaya Basin.
Requires the committee to submit a written report of findings and recommendations,
including any proposed legislative or administrative actions, to the legislature and the David
R. Poynter Legislative Research Library not later than April 1, 2027, and authorizes
supplemental reports as needed.
Provides that the joint legislative committee shall terminate on January 11, 2028.
